h2.div: More information about Covid-19 from the Minnesota Department of Education

div.p: Governor Walz made an announcement to close all schools in Minnesota

div.class: hJDwNd-AhqUyc-c5RTEf purZT-AhqUyc-II5mzb pSzOP-AhqUyc-qWD73c jXK9ad D2fZ2 OjCsFc wHaque GNzUNc

li.a: Minnesota Department of Education Corvid-19 Updates
School Closure Guidance for Public School Districts and Charter Schools

p.strong: Parents/guardians please contact the school by phone or email if your contact information has changed so that the school can contact you about important information and updates.

div.class: hJDwNd-AhqUyc-II5mzb pSzOP-AhqUyc-II5mzb jXK9ad D2fZ2 wHaque GNzUNc

ul.li: Student meals provided by pick up
Day care provided for parents who are service workers
Daily assignments/homework plan for if school closes longer than planned
School closed starting this Monday until after Spring Break: March 16-April 3 - CLOSED
Family Surveys: CSE staff will be contacting parents/guardians by phone to assess family needs and information to help us prepare
Testing Schedules (TBD): Testing suspended until further notice
Intent to Return (TBD): Families will be contacted by phone.

p.em: Thank you families for your patience as we work through this together.
